<p itemprop="description">The head of incident management provides strategic leadership for all incident management activities across the organisation. They establish enterprise-wide incident management frameworks and ensure organisational resilience and service reliability.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide strategic leadership for incident management across the organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish enterprise-wide incident management frameworks and governance</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead organisational resilience and service continuity initiatives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive cultural change towards proactive incident prevention</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Represent incident management interests in executive and board-level discussions</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure alignment with regulatory and compliance requirements</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Develop strategic partnerships for incident management capabilities</li>
    </ul>
</section>

